Package: catgraph
Type: Package
Title: Effect-Size Weighted Association Networks for Categorical Data
Version: 0.10.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Marko", "Orosnjak", email = "marko.orosnjak@uni.lu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
  )
Description: Network-based analysis of multinomial categorical data in two
    complementary layers: a variable-level association network using phi
    and Cramer's V with optional bias correction, and a modality-level
    co-association network on factor levels using phi on cross-variable
    indicator tables. Community detection, bootstrap confidence intervals,
    weighted centrality, and permutation-based tests for cross-group
    structural differences are provided. Designed for descriptive
    exploration of joint categorical structure and for comparing
    categorical association patterns across groups, studies, or
    populations.
